  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      anatomical landmarks on the body surface were used to insert central vein catheter. However,
      ultrasound technique is emerging as a new technique for vein catheterisation. For subclavian
      and femoral vein catheterisation, up to now, there is a lack of evidence of the superiority
      of one technique over the other.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
